<TITLE>RailAmerica Inc.</TITLE>
<META
NAME="keywords" CONTENT="RailAmerica, short line railroads, railroads, transportation, railway">
<META
NAME="description" CONTENT="RailAmerica, Inc. is a short line railroad holding company headquartered in Boca Raton, Florida.  The Company owns and operates short line freight railroads and owns a specialty truck trailer manufacturer."></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="gifs/logo.gif" WIDTH="244" HEIGHT="133"><BR><FONT
SIZE="7" COLOR="#0000A0"><B>RailAmerica</B></FONT></CENTER>
<P><FONT COLOR="#004080"><B><I>RailAmerica, Inc. is a diversified
international short line and regional      railroad holding company
headquartered in Boca Raton, Florida. The Company       owns and operates eleven
short line railroads and provides freight       service over approximately 2,400
miles of track in seven U.S. states and the Republic of Chile.  The Company
holds a minority equity interest in the Great Southern Railway Limited
consortium which operates the 4,000-mile transcontinental Australian passenger
rail service.  RailAmerica also owns a specialty truck trailer manufacturer,    
  Kalyn/Siebert, in Texas.</I></B></FONT></P>
